  "title": "The contribution of smoking to regional mortality differences in the Netherlands",
  "abstract": "Smoking is an important preventable determinant of morbidity and mortality. Knowledge about its role in regional mortality differences can help us to identify relevant policy areas, and to explain national mortality differences.",
